## 🏁 How to Run

1.  **Prerequisites**: Ensure you have Node.js and an active internet connection.
2.  **Environment Setup**: Add your `API_KEYS` (NASA, YouTube, Gemini) to the [backend/.env](file:///c:/Users/admin/OneDrive/Desktop/F.E.PROJ_CSE/AstronomyHub/backend/.env) file.
3.  **One-Click Launch**: Run the [start_all.bat](file:///c:/Users/admin/OneDrive/Desktop/F.E.PROJ_CSE/AstronomyHub/start_all.bat) file in the root directory. 
    - This will launch the Node.js Backend on port `5006`.
    - It will launch the Vite Frontend on its default port.
    - All services are pre-configured to communicate seamlessly.
